Class Instant

An Instant represents a specific instance of universal time with a defined precision. It is loosely based on the same class in the TC39 temporal specification, with added resolution/precision data.

see

https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/blob/master/spec/instant.html

Static fromString

  • fromString(instantToParse: string): Instant
    • Defined in src/common/time/instant.ts:129

    Parses a UTC date string in ISO 8601 format and generates an Instant. The TimeUnit resolution is derived from the amount of information presented. For example if 2018-01-18 is used then TimeUnit.DAYS is the resolution.
